  "markup": "\u003Cp data-start=\u0022252\u0022 data-end=\u0022610\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong data-start=\u0022252\u0022 data-end=\u0022263\u0022\u003EPurpose\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cbr data-start=\u0022263\u0022 data-end=\u0022266\u0022\u003EThe purpose of this policy is to promote employee wellness by providing eligible employees with paid time off to use for personal activities that are important to them. \u201CMe Days\u201D may be used for events such as anniversaries, birthdays, religious or spiritual observances, or simply to take personal time for rest or other meaningful pursuits.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp data-start=\u0022612\u0022 data-end=\u0022743\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong data-start=\u0022612\u0022 data-end=\u0022621\u0022\u003EScope\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cbr data-start=\u0022621\u0022 data-end=\u0022624\u0022\u003EThis policy applies to all full-time employees of Avenu \u0026amp; ITI who meet the eligibility requirements described herein.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp data-start=\u0022745\u0022 data-end=\u0022895\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong data-start=\u0022745\u0022 data-end=\u0022760\u0022\u003EEligibility\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cbr data-start=\u0022760\u0022 data-end=\u0022763\u0022\u003EFull-time employees become eligible to take two (2) paid \u201CMe Days\u201D annually after completing sixty (60) days of active employment.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp data-start=\u0022897\u0022 data-end=\u0022912\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong data-start=\u0022897\u0022 data-end=\u0022910\u0022\u003EProcedure\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Col data-start=\u0022913\u0022 data-end=\u00221779\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cli data-start=\u0022913\u0022 data-end=\u00221438\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp data-start=\u0022916\u0022 data-end=\u0022941\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong data-start=\u0022916\u0022 data-end=\u0022939\u0022\u003ERequesting Time Off\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul data-start=\u0022945\u0022 data-end=\u00221438\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cli data-start=\u0022945\u0022 data-end=\u00221005\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp data-start=\u0022947\u0022 data-end=\u00221005\u0022\u003E\u201CMe Days\u201D must be taken in full-day (8-hour) increments.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli data-start=\u00221009\u0022 data-end=\u00221081\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp data-start=\u00221011\u0022 data-end=\u00221081\u0022\u003EEmployees must submit a request to their manager for specific dates.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli data-start=\u00221085\u0022 data-end=\u00221185\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp data-start=\u00221087\u0022 data-end=\u00221185\u0022\u003EAn automated recording system is available to track and maintain \u201CMe Day\u201D balances and requests.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli data-start=\u00221189\u0022 data-end=\u00221295\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp data-start=\u00221191\u0022 data-end=\u00221295\u0022\u003EManagers may approve or deny requests at their discretion, considering operational and business needs.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli data-start=\u00221299\u0022 data-end=\u00221438\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp data-start=\u00221301\u0022 data-end=\u00221438\u0022\u003EEmployees are encouraged to give advance notice when requesting a \u201CMe Day,\u201D but this is not required if there is no operational impact.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli data-start=\u00221440\u0022 data-end=\u00221779\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp data-start=\u00221443\u0022 data-end=\u00221460\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong data-start=\u00221443\u0022 data-end=\u00221458\u0022\u003ELimitations\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul data-start=\u00221464\u0022 data-end=\u00221779\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cli data-start=\u00221464\u0022 data-end=\u00221610\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp data-start=\u00221466\u0022 data-end=\u00221610\u0022\u003E\u201CMe Days\u201D may not be taken at the beginning or end of a Paid Time Off (PTO) day, adjacent to a company holiday, or used concurrently with PTO.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli data-start=\u00221614\u0022 data-end=\u00221710\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp data-start=\u00221616\u0022 data-end=\u00221710\u0022\u003E\u201CMe Days\u201D do not accrue from year to year and unused days are not paid out upon termination.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli data-start=\u00221714\u0022 data-end=\u00221779\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp data-start=\u00221716\u0022 data-end=\u00221779\u0022\u003E\u201CMe Days\u201D may not be used during an employee\u2019s notice period.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ol\u003E\n\u003Cp data-start=\u00221781\u0022 data-end=\u00222032\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong data-start=\u00221781\u0022 data-end=\u00221799\u0022\u003EResponsibility\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cbr data-start=\u00221799\u0022 data-end=\u00221802\u0022\u003EEmployees are responsible for submitting requests in accordance with this policy and ensuring that their \u201CMe Day\u201D usage is properly recorded. Managers are responsible for reviewing and approving requests based on business needs.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp data-start=\u00222034\u0022 data-end=\u00222176\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong data-start=\u00222034\u0022 data-end=\u00222060\u0022\u003EAdditional Information\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cbr data-start=\u00222060\u0022 data-end=\u00222063\u0022\u003EQuestions regarding \u201CMe Days\u201D should be directed to the employee\u2019s manager or Human Resources Business Partner.\u003C/p\u003E"
}]]></Value>
